♪ I'LL BE READY

01:40.970 --> 01:43.799
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS ♪

01:43.929 --> 01:46.584
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

02:02.165 --> 02:06.909
-[UPBEAT TRANQUIL MUSIC]

02:40.856 --> 02:42.162
-[MITCH LAUGHING]

02:46.775 --> 02:48.429
-I TOLD YOU YOU WAITED
TOO LONG FOR THIS.

02:48.559 --> 02:50.866
-HEY, I MEANT TO
MAKE THAT MOVE, DUDE.

02:50.996 --> 02:52.781
SOMEDAY THEY'RE GONNA
CALL THAT A "BUCHANNON"

02:52.911 --> 02:54.174
IN BOOGIE BOARD COMPETITION.

02:55.566 --> 02:57.002
HEY, WE GOTTA HUSTLE.

02:57.133 --> 02:58.961
I TOLD BEN I'D HAVE
YOU READY TO GO BY 10.

02:59.483 --> 03:00.658
-WHERE'S HE TAKING ME?

03:01.964 --> 03:03.618
-BIG SURPRISE.

03:08.797 --> 03:09.667
-DAD?

03:10.973 --> 03:12.757
YOU KNOW WHEN MOM WAS
HERE FOR THE REUNION?

03:14.281 --> 03:15.891
WELL, WE SORTA TALKED
ABOUT SOMETHING.

03:17.806 --> 03:19.721
-WELL, WHAT DID YOU
SORTA TALK ABOUT?

03:23.681 --> 03:26.162
-WHETHER OR NOT I SHOULD
GO TO SCHOOL BACK IN OHIO.

03:28.295 --> 03:30.601
YOU KNOW, JUST TO AVOID
ALL THE CONFUSION.

03:32.429 --> 03:34.301
AND THEN SPENDING
SUMMERS WITH YOU.

03:35.650 --> 03:36.520
-REALLY?

03:38.087 --> 03:40.045
SHE NEVER SAID ANYTHING
TO ME ABOUT THIS, HOBE.

03:41.090 --> 03:41.917
-WHAT DO YOU THINK I SHOULD DO?

03:43.527 --> 03:44.398
-WHAT DO YOU WANNA DO?

03:45.312 --> 03:47.792
-I DON'T KNOW, I MISS MOM.

03:49.664 --> 03:51.535
BUT IF I GO OVER
THERE, I'LL MISS YOU.

03:52.623 --> 03:53.842
WHAT DO YOU WANT ME TO DO?

03:55.278 --> 03:58.325
-FIRST THING I WANT YOU TO
DO, DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

03:58.455 --> 03:59.587
COME ON, LET'S GO.

04:04.200 --> 04:05.506
-I'LL TALK TO YOUR MOM ABOUT IT.

04:06.376 --> 04:07.551
WE'LL FIGURE OUT
WHAT'S BEST TO DO.

04:08.813 --> 04:10.119
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT, HUH?

04:18.779 --> 04:20.869
-[HOBIE AND MITCH LAUGHING]

04:23.828 --> 04:25.003
-MIKE SAID YOU
WERE LOOKING FOR ME.

04:25.743 --> 04:27.832
-YEAH, YEAH SIT
DOWN, WILL YA, PLEASE?

04:27.963 --> 04:28.964
-[TELEPHONE RINGING]

04:29.094 --> 04:30.095
-SOMETHING WRONG?

04:32.010 --> 04:33.011
-DID YOU EVER GET TO A POINT

04:33.142 --> 04:34.404
WHERE YOU GOTTA MAKE DECISIONS

04:34.926 --> 04:36.363
THAT ARE GONNA CHANGE YOUR LIFE,

04:37.059 --> 04:38.234
AND YOU DON'T KNOW IF
YOU WANNA MAKE 'EM?

04:39.583 --> 04:40.628
-WHAT KIND OF DECISIONS?

04:41.759 --> 04:43.152
-I GOT A LETTER FROM CRAIG.

04:43.283 --> 04:45.110
-CAPTAIN THORPE: AH,
HOW ARE THEY DOING?

04:45.241 --> 04:47.896
-TERRIFIC, THEY GOT A
HOUSE IN CONNECTICUT,

04:48.026 --> 04:49.376
LAW OFFICE IN NEW YORK.

04:49.506 --> 04:50.290
OH, GINA'S PREGNANT.

04:50.420 --> 04:51.378
-REALLY?

04:51.987 --> 04:52.988
THAT'S TERRIFIC.

04:54.032 --> 04:56.034
-HE SAYS HE REPRESENTS
SEAQUEST DIVERS

04:56.165 --> 04:59.211
AND THEY'RE LOOKING
FOR A CONSULTANT/REP
TO WORK CALIFORNIA.

04:59.995 --> 05:01.823
HE'S GOT A JOB
INTERVIEW SET UP FOR ME.

05:01.953 --> 05:03.912
SAYS IT PAYS DOUBLE
WHAT I'M MAKING HERE.

05:06.131 --> 05:08.090
-COULD ALWAYS COUNT ON OLD
CRAIG TO COMPLICATE MATTERS.

05:08.220 --> 05:09.613
-YEAH, BUT THE BIG PROBLEM IS

05:09.744 --> 05:11.093
IT MEANS A HELL OF
A LOT OF TRAVELING,

05:11.223 --> 05:12.442
WHICH MEANS I HAVE
TO LEAVE HOBIE

05:12.573 --> 05:14.226
WITH GAYLE DURING
THE SCHOOL YEAR.

05:14.966 --> 05:16.577
I HAVE NO IDEA WHAT TO DO.

05:18.622 --> 05:21.103
-YOU LOOKING FOR AN OPINION
OR JUST A SOUNDING BOARD?

05:22.322 --> 05:23.192
-BOTH.

05:24.933 --> 05:25.977
-WHY DON'T YOU
TAKE A CATALINA RUN?

05:29.590 --> 05:30.634
-YOU SURE?

05:31.374 --> 05:32.549
-BEST WAY I KNOW
TO CLEAR THE HEAD.

05:33.855 --> 05:34.943
-THANKS.

05:35.073 --> 05:40.035
-[SWELLING UPLIFTING MUSIC]

06:07.932 --> 06:09.412
-[SEAGULLS CRYING]

06:58.287 --> 07:00.507
-MITCH, I JUST REALLY THINK
THAT HE'D BE BETTER OFF

07:00.637 --> 07:02.073
IF HE LIVED WITH ME FULL-TIME.

07:02.204 --> 07:03.553
-NO WAY.

07:03.684 --> 07:05.381
-HE COULD VISIT YOU
EVERY OTHER WEEK.

07:05.512 --> 07:06.687
-YOU CAN FORGET IT!

07:07.209 --> 07:09.037
-CAN YOU JUST PUT YOUR OWN
FEELINGS ASIDE FOR ONCE,

07:09.167 --> 07:10.691
AND THINK ABOUT WHAT'S
BEST FOR YOUR SON?

07:10.821 --> 07:11.648
-I AM.

07:12.867 --> 07:13.824
I ALWAYS DO.

07:15.696 --> 07:17.132
YOU JUST CAN'T HANDLE
IT BECAUSE HE WANTS

07:17.262 --> 07:18.786
TO BE WITH ME MORE THAN
HE WANTS TO BE WITH YOU.

07:18.916 --> 07:20.831
-WELL, OF COURSE HE
WANTS TO BE WITH YOU,

07:20.962 --> 07:22.354
WHAT KID WOULDN'T?

07:23.007 --> 07:26.315
A BLOCK FROM THE OCEAN, A
FATHER WHO SAVES PEOPLE'S LIVES.

07:26.881 --> 07:28.317
HEY, YOU'RE HE HIS HERO.

07:28.448 --> 07:30.450
AND I'M JUST THE OGRE
WHO MAKES HIM STAY

07:30.580 --> 07:32.930
IN HIS BEDROOM DOING HIS
HOMEWORK OVER UNTIL IT'S NEAT.

07:34.149 --> 07:36.499
WITH YOU, LIFE'S A BEACH, WHY
SHOULD HE EVER WANNA LEAVE?

07:36.630 --> 07:37.848
-YOU LEFT.

07:41.025 --> 07:44.202
-MITCH, IT'S TOO LATE
FOR US, BUT NOT FOR HOBIE.

07:44.333 --> 07:46.074
WHAT HE NEEDS NOW
IS CONSISTENCY.

07:46.204 --> 07:47.641
-YOU WANT CONSISTENCY?

07:47.771 --> 07:49.120
I'LL LET HIM VISIT YOU
EVERY OTHER WEEKEND.

07:50.426 --> 07:51.819
-IF HOBIE LIVES WITH ME,

07:51.949 --> 07:53.385
HE'LL HAVE A WHOLE
WORLD FULL OF CHOICES.

07:53.908 --> 07:55.083
WITH YOU, ALL HE'S
EVER GONNA WANNA BE

07:55.213 --> 07:56.867
IS A LIFEGUARD,
JUST LIKE HIS DAD.

07:56.998 --> 07:59.087
-I CAN'T BELIEVE WE'RE STILL
HAVING THIS DAMN ARGUMENT.

08:00.218 --> 08:02.264
NOW, LIFEGUARDS ARE
TEACHERS AND DOCTORS.

08:02.394 --> 08:04.092
CRAIG'S AN ATTORNEY,
FOR GOD'S SAKE.

08:04.222 --> 08:05.223
-YEAH, BUT HE DOESN'T
WANNA BE LIKE THEM,

08:05.354 --> 08:06.660
HE WANTS TO BE LIKE YOU.

08:06.790 --> 08:09.140
[VOICE ECHOING]

08:09.271 --> 08:13.667
-[CONTEMPLATIVE MUSIC]

08:19.760 --> 08:22.589
-[CHILDREN COUGHING]

08:30.945 --> 08:33.337
-STRANGE DAY.
-YEAH, TELL ME ABOUT IT.

08:35.993 --> 08:37.212
I CAN'T STOP
THINKING ABOUT STEVE.

08:37.342 --> 08:38.386
-WHETHER OR NOT
YOU'D DO WHAT HE DID

08:38.518 --> 08:39.693
IF YOU LOST CUSTODY OF HOBIE?

08:39.823 --> 08:41.695
-YEAH, SCARES THE
HELL OUT OF ME.

08:41.825 --> 08:43.260
OH, GOD, WHAT'S THAT?

08:43.392 --> 08:44.436
-WHAT, OH!

08:47.222 --> 08:48.615
YOU EVER THINK ABOUT
GIVING UP ALL THIS STUFF

08:48.745 --> 08:50.138
FOR SOMETHING DRIER
AND MORE LUCRATIVE?

08:50.268 --> 08:51.356
-YEAH, LIKE WHAT?

08:52.749 --> 08:55.491
-THE FIRM GAVE ME A
CHOICE, LAWYER OR LIFEGUARD.

08:55.622 --> 08:57.232
-DOES THAT MEAN
YOU'D QUIT BAYWATCH?

08:58.450 --> 08:59.930
-WE'D STILL HAVE OUR EARLY
MORNING WORKOUTS TOGETHER.

09:00.061 --> 09:01.149
-YEAH AND LOSE YOUR LOCKER.

09:02.672 --> 09:03.847
-YOU'D TAKE AWAY MY LOCKER?

09:03.978 --> 09:04.935
-ABSOLUTELY.

09:05.632 --> 09:07.111
HOW MANY FORMER LIFEGUARDS
HAVE GOT LOCKERS

09:07.242 --> 09:08.156
THAT ARE QUITTERS?

09:08.765 --> 09:09.766
-YOU'D TAKE AWAY MY LOCKER?

09:13.204 --> 09:15.163
WELL, WHAT IF I DONATE
LARGE SUMS OF MONEY

09:15.293 --> 09:17.948
TO THE LIFEGUARD BENEVOLENCE
SOCIETY OR SOMETHING?

09:18.079 --> 09:20.516
-I'D GIVE YOU A NICE PLAQUE
YOU COULD HANG ON YOUR WALL,

09:20.647 --> 09:21.778
THANKING YOU VERY MUCH.

09:22.692 --> 09:24.172
-BUT YOU WON'T LET
ME KEEP MY LOCKER?

09:24.302 --> 09:25.565
-ABSOLUTELY NOT.

09:29.786 --> 09:31.222
-[CHILDREN COUGHING]

09:31.353 --> 09:32.441
DAMN IT!

09:32.572 --> 09:34.791
-WHAT?
-WE'RE BLOCKED.

09:34.922 --> 09:36.010
IT'S THE KIDS.

09:36.140 --> 09:37.751
HEY, OVER HERE!

09:37.881 --> 09:39.187
-YOU GOTTA HELP US!

09:39.317 --> 09:42.190
MY ARMS, MY LEGS,
I CAN'T MOVE THEM.

09:49.066 --> 09:52.069
-HELP, HELP, I CAN'T GET OUT!

09:52.200 --> 09:54.202
-HEY, HEY, HELP!

09:54.332 --> 09:58.772
HEY, HEY, HELP, HELP!

09:59.860 --> 10:03.428
HEY, HEY, OVER HERE, HELP!

10:04.342 --> 10:06.780
MY DAD, WE WERE DIVING,
HE'S DOWN THERE.

10:06.910 --> 10:08.042
HE'S TRAPPED AND
CAN'T GET BACK UP.

10:08.651 --> 10:09.739
YOU GOTTA HELP HIM.

10:12.307 --> 10:13.830
YOU GOTTA HELP HIM.

10:13.961 --> 10:15.397
-WHAT HAPPENED?

10:15.527 --> 10:17.181
-A ROCK, WE WERE UNDER
IT, IT FELL ON HIM.

10:17.312 --> 10:18.530
HE CAN'T GET-- HE'S TRAPPED!

10:18.661 --> 10:20.402
-ALL RIGHT, JUST CALM DOWN.

10:20.532 --> 10:22.230
NOW TELL ME WHAT I NEED TO
KNOW, SO I CAN HELP YOUR DAD.

10:23.448 --> 10:28.323
-[TELEPHONE RINGING]
-[RADIO CHATTER]

10:37.898 --> 10:38.942
-WHO'S THAT?

10:39.682 --> 10:40.727
LET ME GUESS.

10:41.858 --> 10:43.077
CAPTAIN THORPE.

10:44.078 --> 10:45.340
-WHY WOULD HE BE
KISSING YOUR NECK?

10:45.906 --> 10:47.342
-WELL, HE'S A SOUTHERN
CALIFORNIA VAMPIRE.

10:47.472 --> 10:49.213
HE ONLY COMES OUT
IN THE SUNLIGHT.

10:49.344 --> 10:50.737
-I DIDN'T KNOW THAT.

10:50.867 --> 10:51.999
-YEAH, HAVEN'T YOU
NOTICED WHEN HE SMILES,

10:52.129 --> 10:53.478
THE WAY HIS FANGS
KINDA HANG OUT?

10:53.609 --> 10:54.871
-FANGS, YES, DEFINITELY
NOTICED HIS FANGS.

10:55.002 --> 10:56.394
-FANGS HANGING OUT, YEAH.

10:56.917 --> 10:58.179
-MITCH ON RADIO:
BAYWATCH HEADQUARTERS--

10:58.309 --> 11:00.224
[GARBLED RADIO TRANSMISSION]

11:00.355 --> 11:01.269
PLEASE RESPOND.

11:01.399 --> 11:02.749
-THAT'S MITCH.

11:02.879 --> 11:04.359
-SHAUNI, I GOT AN
EMERGENCY SITUATION

11:04.489 --> 11:06.796
ABOUT 10 MILES SOUTHEAST
OF AVALON HARBOR.

11:06.927 --> 11:09.016
I NEED A DIVE TEAM HELO'D
OUT HERE RIGHT AWAY.

11:09.538 --> 11:11.018
-EDDIE'S ON IT,
WHAT'S THE SITUATION?

11:11.148 --> 11:13.890
-L.A. COUNTY LIFEGUARDS
TO COAST GUARD AIR RESCUE.

11:14.021 --> 11:15.849
-I'M ON A BOAT WITH
A 12-YEAR-OLD BOY

11:15.979 --> 11:17.720
WHOSE FATHER IS
TRAPPED UNDERWATER,

11:17.851 --> 11:21.376
APPROXIMATELY 90 FEET DOWN,
AND HE'S RUNNING LOW ON AIR.

11:21.506 --> 11:24.422
HE'S GOT ABOUT 15 TO
20 MINUTES LEFT, MAX.

11:25.032 --> 11:26.163
-DO YOU HAVE ANY
SCUBA GEAR AVAILABLE?

11:26.294 --> 11:28.992
-MASK AND FINS ONLY, NO AIR.

11:29.123 --> 11:30.428
THE BOY EXHAUSTED HIS SUPPLY.

11:31.038 --> 11:32.604
-MAN ON RADIO: COAST GUARD AIR
RESCUE, GO AHEAD, BAYWATCH.

11:32.735 --> 11:33.736
-WE HAVE A DIVER DOWN.

11:33.867 --> 11:35.259
WE NEED EMERGENCY ASSISTANCE.

11:35.390 --> 11:36.913
OUR RESCUE PERSONNEL
WILL AWAIT YOUR ARRIVAL

11:37.044 --> 11:38.698
AT BAYWATCH HEADQUARTERS.

11:38.828 --> 11:40.221
-COAST GUARD RESCUE'S ON
ITS WAY TO BRING US TO YOU.

11:41.831 --> 11:44.094
-I CAN DELAY 10 MINUTES,
AND THEN I HAVE TO FREE-DIVE.

11:44.791 --> 11:46.662
-NO, 90 FEET'S TOO DEEP.

11:47.228 --> 11:49.099
IT'D BE A ONE-WAY DIVE,
HE'D NEVER MAKE IT.

11:49.230 --> 11:51.841
-THEY'LL BE THERE, MITCH,
DON'T FREE-DIVE, IT'S TOO RISKY.

11:52.494 --> 11:55.932
-IF YOU'RE NOT HERE IN 10
MINUTES, I WON'T HAVE A CHOICE.

11:56.498 --> 11:57.717
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

11:57.847 --> 11:58.848
-I'M ON MY WAY.

12:30.010 --> 12:31.663
-[MUFFLED SCREAMING]

12:35.319 --> 12:37.365
-MAN ON RADIO: BAYWATCH 295,
COAST GUARD AIR RESCUE,

12:37.495 --> 12:39.671
SOUTHWEST APPROACH,
REQUEST PERMISSION TO LAND.

12:39.802 --> 12:41.238
-MAN ON RADIO #2: COAST
GUARD AIR RESCUE,

12:41.369 --> 12:43.632
THIS IS BAYWATCH 295,
YOU ARE CLEAR TO LAND.

12:43.763 --> 12:44.981
AREA IS CLEAR.

12:50.465 --> 12:53.642
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

12:58.038 --> 12:59.691
-COAST GUARD: COME ON,
LET'S GO, LET'S GO.

12:59.822 --> 13:00.823
ALL RIGHT, THEY'RE IN.

13:06.873 --> 13:08.309
-MAN ON RADIO: COAST
GUARD AIR RESCUE

13:08.439 --> 13:09.832
TO L.A. INTERNATIONAL
AIR TRAFFIC CONTROL,

13:09.963 --> 13:11.312
REQUEST PERMISSION
FOR EMERGENCY PASSAGE

13:11.442 --> 13:13.880
THROUGH TRAFFIC PATTERN,
LOW-LEVEL ALTITUDE.

13:14.010 --> 13:15.403
DEADHEAD, CATALINA.

13:15.533 --> 13:17.535
COMMENCING VISUAL SEARCH
FOR DOWNED DIVER, OVER.

13:18.101 --> 13:20.364
-MAN ON RADIO #2: ROGER, COAST
GUARD, CLEAR TO PROCEED.

13:23.846 --> 13:24.847
-[DIVER WAILING]

13:30.853 --> 13:32.202
-WHEN ARE THEY GONNA GET HERE?

13:33.116 --> 13:33.943
-ANY MINUTE.

13:35.553 --> 13:38.208
WHEN THEY DO, TELL 'EM I WENT
DOWN AFTER YOUR DAD AT 1:58.

13:38.861 --> 13:40.341
-BUT THEY SAID YOU WOULDN'T
BE ABLE TO GET BACK UP.

13:42.038 --> 13:43.997
-HOPEFULLY THEY'LL
GET DOWN TO ME IN TIME.

13:44.867 --> 13:46.434
AND I'LL HAVE YOUR
DAD FREED BY THEN.

13:48.262 --> 13:49.567
DON'T WORRY, IT'LL BE OKAY.

13:52.092 --> 13:54.659
[INHALING AND EXHALING]

14:24.124 --> 14:25.081
-[STRUGGLING]

14:37.877 --> 14:39.095
[DIVER SHOUTING]

14:44.448 --> 14:46.189
-MAN ON RADIO: COAST
GUARD AIR RESCUE

14:46.320 --> 14:47.799
TO L.A.X. TRAFFIC CONTROL,
WE ARE EXITING YOUR AIRSPACE.

14:47.930 --> 14:49.801
HEADING, 33 SOUTHWEST, OVER.

14:50.324 --> 14:51.716
-MAN ON RADIO #2: ROGER, AIR
RESCUE, YOU'RE CLEAR.

15:23.052 --> 15:24.010
-[MITCH BREATHING]

15:26.838 --> 15:29.754
-[DIVER STRUGGLING
AND EXCLAIMING]

15:35.891 --> 15:38.372
-MAN ON RADIO: BAYWATCH 295,
COAST GUARD AIR RESCUE.

15:38.502 --> 15:39.764
WE HAVE VISUAL CONTACT.

15:42.332 --> 15:47.033
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

16:21.502 --> 16:22.982
-[MITCH GASPING]

16:26.855 --> 16:28.161
-MAN ON RADIO: WE
HAVE VICTIM IN SIGHT.

16:28.291 --> 16:30.554
SETTING UP TO MOVE
INTO DROP POSITION.

16:30.685 --> 16:32.121
READY, FROGMAN?

16:32.252 --> 16:32.992
-MAN: WE'RE HOLDING
STEADY, GO WHEN READY.

16:36.647 --> 16:38.823
OKAY, HE'S CLEAR
TO THE LEFT, GO!

16:44.220 --> 16:45.830
-WOMAN ON RADIO: THIS IS
CATALINA DECOMPRESSION UNIT.

16:45.961 --> 16:48.137
WE HAVE RECEIVED YOUR
TRAFFIC, AND ARE STANDING BY.

16:48.659 --> 16:49.921
-MAN ON RADIO:
ROGER, CATALINA.

16:50.052 --> 16:51.314
DROPPED AND LOWERING
INTO POSITION.

16:52.707 --> 16:54.926
DIVERS HAVE VICTIMS, AND ARE
SWIMMING TOWARDS THE BASKET.

16:55.710 --> 16:58.365
E.T.A., CATALINA,
THREE MINUTES, OVER.

16:58.887 --> 17:00.845
-WOMAN ON RADIO: ROGER, AIR
RESCUE, CATALINA OUT.

17:02.934 --> 17:04.632
-DOCTOR: THROUGH
THE DOORS, GO, GO, GO.

17:04.762 --> 17:05.633
-DOCTOR #2: I GOT IT.

17:07.026 --> 17:08.114
-DOCTOR: THROUGH
THE HALLWAY, PLEASE.

17:10.594 --> 17:11.508
-[MITCH GROANING]

17:12.727 --> 17:13.510
-DOCTOR:
COMING THROUGH HERE.

17:22.214 --> 17:23.694
-DOCTOR #2: DOOR,
DOOR, GET THE DOOR.

17:23.825 --> 17:24.694
-DOCTOR: OKAY, GOT IT.

17:26.915 --> 17:27.959
-HERE, WE'RE ALL SET.

17:35.054 --> 17:36.359
-THE VITALS ARE
WEAK AND FADING.

17:36.881 --> 17:38.100
-WHERE'S THE OTHER TANK?

17:38.622 --> 17:39.580
-IT'S DOWN, ONLY
ONE'S FUNCTIONAL.

17:39.710 --> 17:41.538
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

17:41.669 --> 17:42.757
-PUT HIM IN FIRST.

17:42.887 --> 17:44.367
-ALL RIGHT, PUT HIM IN.

17:47.631 --> 17:48.937
HOW DEEP WERE YOU?

17:49.633 --> 17:52.027
-I DON'T KNOW,
90, 100 FEET MAYBE.

17:54.769 --> 17:56.945
-MITCH, IT WON'T TAKE US
LONG TO BRING YOU BACK.

17:57.076 --> 17:57.859
LET'S PUT YOU IN FIRST.

17:57.989 --> 17:58.903
-NO.

18:01.210 --> 18:02.255
-DOCTOR: EASY, WATCH IT.

18:06.650 --> 18:08.435
-COME ON, IT COULD TAKE
SIX, MAYBE EIGHT HOURS

18:08.565 --> 18:09.566
TO GET THIS GUY UNBENT.

18:09.697 --> 18:11.090
-JUST GET ME BACK UNDERWATER.

18:11.220 --> 18:12.656
-YOU RISKED YOUR LIFE
ONCE FOR THIS GUY.

18:12.787 --> 18:14.397
-I DIDN'T DO ANYTHING
IF THE GUY DIES.

18:14.528 --> 18:15.746
-WHAT IF YOU DIE?

18:15.877 --> 18:17.096
-I'M NOT GONNA--
[EXCLAIMS PAINFULLY]

18:17.835 --> 18:18.836
GOD.

18:26.583 --> 18:28.716
-ALL RIGHT, PRESSURIZE
TO THREE ATMOSPHERES.

18:32.023 --> 18:33.503
-HOW LONG TO DECOMPRESS HIM?

18:34.156 --> 18:35.549
-HE'S IN PRETTY BAD SHAPE.

18:35.679 --> 18:37.246
FIVE, SIX HOURS, MAYBE LONGER.

18:39.770 --> 18:40.641
-WHAT?

18:41.555 --> 18:43.687
LOOK, HE CAN'T MAKE IT
THAT LONG, LOOK AT HIM.

18:45.254 --> 18:46.081
ALL RIGHT, LOOK.

18:46.908 --> 18:48.866
WHAT IF WE PUT HIM BACK
IN THE WATER AT THE DEPTH,

18:48.997 --> 18:50.564
TILL HIS TANK IS READY, HUH?

18:51.086 --> 18:53.523
-AT THIS POINT,
IT'D LIKELY KILL HIM.

18:55.003 --> 18:57.048
-YOU AND ME, WE GOTTA PUT
HIM BACK ON THE HELICOPTER.

18:57.179 --> 18:58.485
-NOW, WAIT A SECOND.

18:59.007 --> 19:00.922
ANY ALTITUDE COULD
BRING ON A SEIZURE,

19:01.052 --> 19:02.750
POSSIBLY PARALYSIS, MAYBE WORSE.

19:02.880 --> 19:04.795
-LOOK, WE GOT A CHAMBER
BACK AT BAYWATCH.

19:04.926 --> 19:06.667
ALL YOU'RE TELLING ME IS
WE CAN'T TAKE HIM THERE,

19:06.797 --> 19:08.190
AND YOU CAN'T TAKE HIM HERE,

19:08.321 --> 19:09.583
WHAT THE HELL ARE WE
SUPPOSED TO DO, HUH?

19:10.192 --> 19:11.933
-WELL, I'LL TRY TO GET HIM IN
HERE AS QUICKLY AS POSSIBLE.

19:12.063 --> 19:13.282
-WHAT ABOUT A SPEEDBOAT?

19:14.065 --> 19:15.850
-HOW MUCH TIME DOES HE HAVE?

19:15.980 --> 19:17.939
-NOT ENOUGH TIME FOR A BOAT
RIDE TO THE MAINLAND, NO WAY.

19:19.462 --> 19:21.551
-ALL RIGHT, SO LET ME GET
SOMETHING STRAIGHT HERE.

19:22.161 --> 19:24.641
IF WE FLY JUST ABOVE THE WATER,
HE SHOULD BE SAFE, RIGHT?

19:24.772 --> 19:25.773
-NOT NECESSARILY AT ALL.

19:25.903 --> 19:26.904
-IS HE GONNA SURVIVE IT OR NOT?

19:27.035 --> 19:28.428
-YES, POSSIBLY,

19:28.558 --> 19:30.517
BUT YOU BETTER MAKE SURE
THEY SKIM THE WATER.

19:30.647 --> 19:31.909
-COAST GUARD
PILOTS ARE THE BEST.

19:32.040 --> 19:33.172
IF ANYONE COULD DO IT, THEY CAN.

19:33.302 --> 19:35.348
-[MACHINES BEEPING]

19:38.525 --> 19:41.136
-[MITCH GROANING AND SIGHING]

19:41.832 --> 19:42.703
HOBIE?

19:52.103 --> 19:53.844
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

19:53.975 --> 19:56.107
-YOU'RE STILL GROUNDED FOR A
MONTH, AND I'M STILL MAD AT YOU.

19:56.238 --> 19:57.805
-I'M STILL MAD AT YOU.

19:58.414 --> 19:59.894
-YOU'RE MAD AT ME, WHY?

20:00.024 --> 20:01.983
-FOR HAVING DEVIN SNEAK
US OUT THE BACK WAY,

20:02.113 --> 20:03.724
AND TELLING THOSE
REPORTERS NO ONE WAS THERE

20:03.854 --> 20:05.247
WHEN YOU FOUND MY GADGETS.

20:06.509 --> 20:07.945
I COULD HAVE BEEN FAMOUS, DAD.

20:08.076 --> 20:09.469
-ALL RIGHT, LET'S GET
ONE THING STRAIGHT.

20:10.513 --> 20:12.559
WHAT YOU DID WAS
DANGEROUS AND DUMB.

20:13.168 --> 20:15.083
A MAN'S BEEN KILLED,
BOATS HAVE BEEN SUNK,

20:15.214 --> 20:16.650
SOME LUNATIC WAS READY

20:16.780 --> 20:18.695
TO BLOW UP THE STORM
DRAIN WITH YOU IN IT!

20:18.826 --> 20:20.871
IT'S NO TIME FOR A
PRACTICAL JOKE, HOBIE.

20:21.002 --> 20:22.308
NO MATTER HOW CLEVER.

20:26.964 --> 20:28.662
COME HERE A MINUTE, SIT DOWN.

20:32.927 --> 20:35.973
LOOK, I KNOW YOU WERE
JUST BEING 10 YEARS OLD.

20:39.238 --> 20:41.414
BUT IF ANYTHING EVER
HAPPENED TO YOU, MAN,

20:42.719 --> 20:43.981
I DON'T KNOW WHAT I'D DO.

20:47.637 --> 20:48.856
I COULDN'T LIVE WITHOUT YOU.

20:52.642 --> 20:53.861
-I'M REALLY SORRY.

20:56.342 --> 20:58.213
-JUST USE YOUR HEAD
FROM NOW ON, OKAY?

20:58.735 --> 20:59.910
-I WILL.
-OKAY.

21:00.650 --> 21:01.434
-I SWEAR.

21:03.174 --> 21:04.045
DAD?

21:04.915 --> 21:05.786
-YEAH?

21:07.135 --> 21:08.267
-I LOVE YOU.

21:10.486 --> 21:11.618
-I LOVE YOU TOO.

21:11.748 --> 21:16.666
-[HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING]

21:47.262 --> 21:48.524
-DON'T DIE, MITCH!

21:50.134 --> 21:51.135
DON'T DIE!

21:52.528 --> 21:54.269
COME ON, MAN, JUST
HANG IN THERE.

21:55.009 --> 21:56.315
COME ON, JUST HANG IN THERE.

21:56.445 --> 21:58.099
NOT MUCH LONGER,
WE'RE ALMOST THERE.

21:58.229 --> 22:01.711
-[SNAKE HISSING AND RATTLING]

22:08.718 --> 22:11.765
[SNAKE RATTLING]

22:27.346 --> 22:30.261
-[EXCLAIMING]

22:30.392 --> 22:34.265
[GASPING]

22:58.377 --> 22:59.290
[MITCH GROANING]

23:01.597 --> 23:02.468
-YOU ARE A MESS.

23:04.121 --> 23:05.732
I GOT YOU, READY?

23:05.862 --> 23:08.343
ONE, TWO, THREE, I GOT YOU.

23:08.474 --> 23:09.344
HERE WE GO.

23:11.477 --> 23:12.782
THERE.
-[MITCH GROANING]

23:16.786 --> 23:18.309
-WHAT DO YOU THINK?

23:18.440 --> 23:19.006
-I THINK IT'S BETTER
IF YOU PUT ME OVER THERE.

23:19.136 --> 23:20.486
-OH, WHAT?

23:20.616 --> 23:22.313
-THE OTHER SIDE OF
THE FIRE IS BETTER.

23:23.097 --> 23:24.881
THE LEAST YOU COULD DO
IS GET SOME BRANCHES

23:25.012 --> 23:26.405
AND SOME BIGGER LOGS.

23:26.535 --> 23:27.797
THIS THING WILL LAST
US ABOUT 20 MINUTES.

23:27.928 --> 23:29.843
-I FOUND THE CAVE,
I BUILT THE FIRE.

23:29.973 --> 23:31.235
I KNOW WHAT I'M
SUPPOSED TO PUT IN IT.

23:31.366 --> 23:33.063
-WHY ARE YOU GETTING
TESTY WITH ME?

23:33.194 --> 23:35.675
I'M THE ONE WITH THE BROKEN
LEG AND THE SNAKE BITE HERE.

23:35.805 --> 23:37.154
-YOU'RE ALSO THE ONE
WITH A STRANGE WAY

23:37.285 --> 23:38.286
OF SHOWING YOUR APPRECIATION.

23:38.895 --> 23:40.593
-[EXCLAIMING PAINFULLY]

23:46.512 --> 23:47.556
-DOES THIS HURT?

23:47.687 --> 23:49.645
-AH, OF COURSE THAT HURTS!

23:49.776 --> 23:51.081
[VOICE ECHOING]

23:51.212 --> 23:52.692
-EDDIE: WE'RE
ALMOST THERE, MITCH.

23:52.822 --> 23:54.868
JUST HANG IN THERE,
BUDDY, WE'RE ALMOST THERE.

24:18.979 --> 24:21.329
-MAN ON RADIO: BAYWATCH 295,
THIS IS COAST GUARD AIR RESCUE.

24:21.895 --> 24:23.636
WE ARE ON FINAL APPROACH,
REQUESTING PERMISSION

24:23.766 --> 24:24.767
FOR EMERGENCY
LANDING WITH VICTIM

24:24.898 --> 24:26.334
IN CRITICAL CONDITION, OVER.

24:26.465 --> 24:27.988
-MAN #2: YEAH,
ROGER, AIR RESCUE.

24:28.118 --> 24:29.555
LANDING AREA IS CLEAR
HERE, WE ARE STANDING BY.

24:36.997 --> 24:38.477
-EDDIE: ALL RIGHT,
WE'RE HERE, MITCH.

24:38.607 --> 24:40.174
JUST HANG ON THERE, BUDDY.

24:40.304 --> 24:42.306
-THAT'S RIGHT, MITCH, YOU'RE
HOME WITH YOUR OWN NOW.

24:42.872 --> 24:44.091
YOU'RE GONNA PULL
THROUGH THIS JUST FINE.

24:44.744 --> 24:45.527
-EDDIE: ARE HOBIE
AND BEN BACK YET?

24:45.658 --> 24:47.007
-NO, NOT YET.

24:47.137 --> 24:48.225
-HAVING HOBIE HERE
COULD MAKE A DIFFERENCE.

24:48.356 --> 24:49.183
-FIND HIM.

24:49.313 --> 24:50.097
WATCH HIS HEAD.

24:50.227 --> 24:51.533
-MEN: EASY, EASY.

24:51.664 --> 24:52.447
-SWING HIM AROUND THERE.

24:52.578 --> 24:53.492
-EDDIE: WATCH HIM.

24:54.754 --> 24:55.755
-THIS WAY.

24:55.885 --> 24:56.886
-GOOD, GOOD.

24:58.061 --> 24:59.019
-WATCH HIS HEAD.

25:00.411 --> 25:01.282
-LIFT HIM.

25:02.588 --> 25:03.502
-HIS MASK.

25:03.632 --> 25:04.546
-LET'S GET THIS THING UP.

25:06.374 --> 25:07.636
-WATCH THE LINE.

25:12.685 --> 25:13.729
-I'LL TAKE THAT.

25:17.298 --> 25:18.821
-EDDIE: HOW BAD IS HE?

25:18.952 --> 25:20.170
-HE'S GOT A LOT OF NITROGEN
TRAPPED IN HIS SYSTEM.

25:20.301 --> 25:21.520
HOLD THIS TILL I GET
A PRESSURE SEAL.

25:23.739 --> 25:25.698
-NOTHING'S GOING ON,
LET'S JUST DROP IT.

25:26.437 --> 25:27.308
-MITCH: LET'S NOT.

25:28.527 --> 25:29.615
-OH, THIS IS GREAT.

25:30.311 --> 25:31.965
LET'S HAVE A PARTY, HUH?

25:32.487 --> 25:34.445
WHY DON'T YOU CALL CAPTAIN
THORPE AND THE CHIEF?

25:34.576 --> 25:36.273
-NOW STICK AROUND,
STICK AROUND.

25:36.404 --> 25:37.666
WE GOT LOTS TO TALK ABOUT.

25:38.928 --> 25:40.669
-IT WAS A LONG TIME AGO.

25:47.458 --> 25:49.983
IT WAS LIKE ANOTHER
LIFE, YOU KNOW?

25:56.990 --> 26:00.559
WE MET IN A FOSTER HOME AND...

26:02.865 --> 26:03.736
WE WERE TIGHT.

26:04.867 --> 26:08.088
WE USED TO RUN TOGETHER,
WE'D GO TO MOVIES TOGETHER.

26:08.218 --> 26:09.480
WE JUST HUNG OUT.

26:10.090 --> 26:12.309
WE EVEN TALKED ABOUT COMING
TO CALIFORNIA TOGETHER.

26:13.876 --> 26:15.922
THEN ONE DAY, WE WENT
INTO THIS LIQUOR STORE.

26:16.618 --> 26:19.534
AND I WANTED TO
BUY A BAG OF CHIPS.

26:22.711 --> 26:24.495
AND THEN JIMMY
PULLS OUT THIS GUN.

26:25.105 --> 26:25.932
I DIDN'T EVEN KNOW HE OWNED ONE.

26:27.237 --> 26:28.804
AND HE SAYS, "THIS
IS A STICKUP."

26:29.718 --> 26:31.981
AND I SAID, "WHAT DO
YOU THINK YOU'RE DOING?"

26:32.112 --> 26:34.070
AND THEN HE SHOVED ME,
AND I SHOVED HIM BACK.

26:34.723 --> 26:35.811
AND THEN THE GUY
BEHIND THE COUNTER

26:35.942 --> 26:37.160
PULLS OUT A GUN OF HIS OWN.

26:40.163 --> 26:41.512
AND THEN THE NEXT THING I KNOW,

26:41.643 --> 26:43.253
I'M TAKING RIDE
BACK DOWN TO COUNTY JAIL.

26:44.080 --> 26:44.994
-HOW OLD WERE YOU?

26:46.474 --> 26:47.649
-16.

26:48.171 --> 26:49.608
THINGS IN LIFE YOU WANNA
PUT BEHIND YOU FOREVER.

26:49.738 --> 26:51.522
I GUESS THAT'S JUST
NOT POSSIBLE, IS IT?

26:52.132 --> 26:52.959
-MAYBE NOT.

26:54.351 --> 26:55.570
BUT YOU CAN START OVER.

26:55.701 --> 26:57.746
-TIME TO HANG UP
THE GLOVES, CHAMP.

27:02.577 --> 27:03.447
-YOU'RE RIGHT.

27:04.884 --> 27:07.234
-SUSPENSION'S OVER,
YOU'RE BACK ON THE BEACH.

27:08.583 --> 27:10.150
-YOU'RE KIDDING?
-NO, I'M NOT KIDDING.

27:10.280 --> 27:11.934
EDDIE, YOU CAME CLEAN WITH ME.

27:12.543 --> 27:14.154
YOU'VE COME A LONG WAY
SINCE PHILADELPHIA.

27:14.284 --> 27:16.417
AND MAYBE I'D LIKE TO
SEE YOU GO THE DISTANCE.

27:16.547 --> 27:18.506
[VOICE ECHOING]

27:23.859 --> 27:29.299
[MITCH GASPING AND GROANING]

27:31.562 --> 27:32.694
-OKAY, EDDIE.

27:34.391 --> 27:39.701
-[AIR HISSING]
-[MACHINE BEEPING]

27:39.832 --> 27:42.182
-[MITCH EXCLAIMING]

27:44.401 --> 27:45.707
-HE'S HAVING A SEIZURE!

27:45.838 --> 27:50.233
-[MITCH EXCLAIMING
AND SCREAMING]

27:51.539 --> 27:53.106
-LOOK AT HIM, HE'S GOING CRAZY.

27:53.976 --> 27:55.456
IS THERE SOMETHING
WE CAN GIVE HIM?

27:57.371 --> 27:59.155
-NO, HE JUST HAS
TO FIGHT THROUGH IT.

27:59.286 --> 28:01.375
-I TOLD HIM NOT TO DIVE.

28:03.029 --> 28:04.552
-DID YOU REALLY
EXPECT HIM NOT TO?

28:04.683 --> 28:07.207
-[MACHINES BEEPING]

28:07.816 --> 28:09.688
-WE'RE PRESSURIZING HIM
BACK DOWN TO 90 FEET.

28:10.819 --> 28:11.907
THEN ALL WE CAN DO IS WAIT.

28:12.038 --> 28:13.300
AND BRING HIM BACK ONE FOOT

28:13.430 --> 28:14.780
AT A TIME TO THE
SURFACE PRESSURE.

28:15.998 --> 28:18.784
-[MACHINES BEEPING]

28:18.914 --> 28:23.353
-[HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING]

28:23.484 --> 28:28.402
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

29:21.455 --> 29:22.543
-HOBIE!

30:01.277 --> 30:06.021
-[HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING]

30:53.112 --> 30:58.030
[HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING]

31:39.114 --> 31:40.202
-[SEAGULL CRYING]

31:47.079 --> 31:47.906
-HEY.

31:48.950 --> 31:50.560
WE JUST HEARD FROM CATALINA.

31:50.691 --> 31:52.519
AND THE MAN THAT MITCH
BROUGHT UP IS GONNA BE FINE.

31:53.172 --> 31:53.999
-GOOD.

31:55.783 --> 31:57.567
-EDDIE, YOU DID
EVERYTHING THAT YOU COULD.

32:00.527 --> 32:02.311
-IF MITCH DIES, I
DIDN'T DO ANYTHING.

32:08.970 --> 32:10.537
-[SIGHING]

32:16.021 --> 32:20.982
-[MACHINE BEEPING]
-[AIR HISSING]

32:29.295 --> 32:33.386
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

32:37.868 --> 32:42.612
-[MACHINES BEEPING]

32:58.411 --> 32:59.847
-WHY DON'T TAKE HIM
HOME, GET SOME REST?

33:00.369 --> 33:01.718
I'LL LET YOU KNOW IF
THERE'S ANY CHANGE.

33:02.328 --> 33:03.459
-WE'RE NOT GONNA LEAVE.

33:03.982 --> 33:05.461
NOBODY IS, YOU KNOW THAT.

33:06.071 --> 33:07.463
NOT UNTIL WE KNOW HE'S SAFE.

33:09.726 --> 33:10.597
-TALK TO HIM.

33:11.902 --> 33:13.165
CAN'T HURT, KEEP HIM ALERT.

33:24.219 --> 33:25.046
-HEY, MITCH.

33:26.613 --> 33:28.136
I KNOW YOU CAN HEAR ME.

33:30.138 --> 33:31.835
SO YOU LISTEN TO ME, OKAY?

33:33.011 --> 33:34.229
YOU HANG IN THERE.

33:35.709 --> 33:36.840
BECAUSE WE NEED YOU.

33:38.712 --> 33:40.931
NONE OF US ARE GONNA MAKE
IT WITHOUT YOU, LIEUTENANT.

33:42.324 --> 33:43.238
YOU HANG IN THERE.

33:46.720 --> 33:48.417
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

33:48.548 --> 33:50.898
-I'M NOT GONNA TELL
YOU HOW TO DO YOUR JOBS.

33:51.725 --> 33:54.249
SOME OF YOU HAVE BEEN
LIFEGUARDS AS LONG AS I HAVE,

33:54.380 --> 33:55.772
SOME OF YOU EVEN LONGER.

33:56.382 --> 33:58.688
SO JUST DO ME A FAVOR, HUH?

33:58.819 --> 33:59.994
MAKE ME LOOK GOOD.

34:01.039 --> 34:01.909
THAT'S IT.

34:03.389 --> 34:05.739
OH, YEAH, SURF'S THREE TO
FIVE, VERY SHORT INTERVALS.

34:05.869 --> 34:07.175
THERE'S GONNA BE A LOT
OF WATER ON THE BEACH.

34:07.306 --> 34:08.481
RIPTIDES WILL BE PULLING.

34:08.610 --> 34:10.004
I WANT PREVENTIONS
OUT THERE, OKAY?

34:10.612 --> 34:12.179
LISTEN, IF YOU GUYS
GOT ANY BACKUPS,

34:12.311 --> 34:13.833
CALL 'EM TO SIT OVER HERE, HUH?

34:13.964 --> 34:15.574
HEY, EDDIE, CAN I TALK
TO YOU FOR A SECOND?

34:15.705 --> 34:16.924
SHAUNI.

34:17.489 --> 34:18.404
JIM.

34:19.056 --> 34:21.014
YOU'RE IN TOWER 27 TODAY.
-NO WAY.

34:21.146 --> 34:22.495
-EXCUSE ME, I'LL
GET RIGHT TO YOU.

34:22.625 --> 34:23.931
-BUT I WANT 27.

34:24.062 --> 34:25.759
I HANG OUT THERE.

34:25.889 --> 34:27.239
I KNOW THE BEACH, AND I KNOW
THE ALL THE INSHORE HOLES.

34:27.369 --> 34:28.891
MY FRIENDS ARE EXPECTING ME.

34:29.023 --> 34:31.112
-NAH, YOU'RE NOT HANGING
OUT TODAY, YOU'RE WORKING.

34:33.201 --> 34:35.985
TOWER 27 IS RIGHT NEXT
TO THE SAND AND SEA CLUB.

34:36.117 --> 34:37.510
THEY GOT THEIR OWN LIFEGUARD,

34:37.639 --> 34:38.946
BUT WE KINDA KNOW
HOW HE WATCHES WATER.

34:39.077 --> 34:40.513
-THEN HE DOESN'T EXIST.

34:40.643 --> 34:42.210
-FOR ALL INTENTS AND PURPOSES.

34:42.819 --> 34:45.561
ALSO, REMEMBER, KEEP AN
EYE ON THE RESCUE CAN OF
THE TOWER NEXT TO YOU.

34:45.692 --> 34:47.868
IF IT'S MISSING, YOU BETTER
FIND OUT WHERE THE LIFEGUARD IS.

34:47.998 --> 34:49.304
-YOU GOT IT.

34:49.435 --> 34:51.176
-YOU ARE ON RESCUE
BOAT WITH JILLIAN.

34:51.306 --> 34:52.612
-ON A BOAT?

34:52.742 --> 34:54.483
-OH, THANK YOU SO
MUCH, LIEUTENANT.

34:54.614 --> 34:56.746
-I DO NOT WANNA BE STUCK
OUT ON A BOAT ALL DAY.

34:56.877 --> 34:58.705
-FINE, YOU'RE GONNA
HAVE TO CHANGE THE SUIT.

34:59.358 --> 35:00.794
-WHAT'S WRONG WITH IT?

35:00.924 --> 35:02.361
THEY SAID GIRLS GET TO
BUY THEIR OWN SUITS.

35:02.491 --> 35:04.189
-YEAH, BUT THERE'S NO
LIFEGUARD PATCH ON IT.

35:04.319 --> 35:05.799
YOU GOT AN EXTRA ONE, DON'T YOU?

35:07.017 --> 35:09.107
-[SCOFFS] I CAN SEW
THE PATCH ON THIS ONE.

35:09.237 --> 35:10.325
-WHERE?

35:14.764 --> 35:16.636
-I'M SURE THERE'S SOME
SWIMSUITS IN THE LOCKER ROOM.

35:16.766 --> 35:18.246
-SHAUNI, COME
HERE FOR A SECOND.

35:18.986 --> 35:20.683
WHEN YOU'RE READY TO
BE PUT IN A TOWER,

35:20.814 --> 35:22.729
I'LL PUT YOU IN
ONE, DON'T WORRY.

35:23.251 --> 35:24.426
-MITCH.

35:25.906 --> 35:27.299
YOU CHANGED MY LIFE.

35:29.170 --> 35:31.738
DON'T YOU GIVE UP, YOU FIGHT!

35:33.522 --> 35:34.306
YOU FIGHT.

35:34.436 --> 35:37.657
-[MACHINES BEEPING]

35:37.787 --> 35:42.792
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

35:45.230 --> 35:46.100
-[EXHALES]

35:46.883 --> 35:47.754
HEY.

35:49.538 --> 35:50.670
HEY, I'M OKAY!

35:51.540 --> 35:52.585
LET ME OUT OF HERE.

35:53.455 --> 35:55.327
[KNOCKING]
HEY, HEY!

35:56.284 --> 35:57.329
HEY.

35:57.459 --> 35:59.331
I'M OKAY, LET ME OUT OF HERE.

36:00.984 --> 36:02.160
ANYBODY OUT THERE?

36:21.831 --> 36:22.702
HEY.

36:24.356 --> 36:25.270
HEY!

36:28.186 --> 36:29.622
PRETTY FUNNY,
IGNORING ME, I KNOW.

36:29.752 --> 36:30.753
BIG JOKE, HUH?

36:31.624 --> 36:33.016
I'VE BEEN THROUGH HELL HERE.

36:37.412 --> 36:38.196
HOBIE.

36:38.326 --> 36:39.588
-DAD.

36:40.937 --> 36:42.112
-HOW'S HE DOING, CAP?

36:43.810 --> 36:45.333
-I'M FINE.

36:45.464 --> 36:46.726
-THEY'VE GOT HIM UP TO
ONE ATMOSPHERE, BUDDY.

36:46.856 --> 36:48.293
HE'S JUST NOT
RESPONDING ANYMORE.

36:49.337 --> 36:50.208
-HOBIE.

36:51.992 --> 36:53.036
HOBIE, I'M HERE.

37:04.352 --> 37:05.223
HOBIE?

37:09.836 --> 37:10.880
-DAD.

37:11.011 --> 37:12.230
I WANNA GO IN THERE WITH HIM.

37:13.405 --> 37:14.580
-YOU CAN'T DO THAT, HOBE.

37:15.233 --> 37:16.016
-WHY NOT?

37:16.146 --> 37:17.278
I COULD FIT.

37:18.061 --> 37:19.498
-WE CAN'T OPEN THE TANK

37:19.628 --> 37:21.239
UNTIL THE PRESSURE'S
BACK TO NORMAL, HOBIE.

37:38.343 --> 37:39.996
-SOMEBODY DO SOMETHING.

37:40.127 --> 37:41.171
-OVER HERE.

37:41.998 --> 37:43.130
YOU TALK TO HIM, OKAY?

37:45.219 --> 37:46.133
TELL HIM YOU LOVE HIM.

37:47.526 --> 37:49.789
-YOU BETTER REPRESSURIZE
HIM BACK DOWN AGAIN.

37:50.398 --> 37:51.225
-I KNOW.

37:51.965 --> 37:53.532
I JUST HOPE HIS
BODY CAN TAKE IT.

37:56.056 --> 37:57.536
-[AIR HISSING]

38:01.279 --> 38:03.106
[AIR HISSING]

38:03.237 --> 38:04.107
-DAD?

38:05.848 --> 38:10.723
DAD, I KNOW YOU'RE SICK, BUT
PLEASE DON'T DIE, PLEASE.

38:15.902 --> 38:17.556
I'LL STAY HERE WITH YOU, DAD.

38:18.731 --> 38:21.081
I PROMISE, I WON'T LEAVE YOU.

38:21.734 --> 38:24.302
-[MITCH SHIVERING]

38:24.432 --> 38:29.307
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

38:34.050 --> 38:36.314
-DAD, PLEASE COME BACK.

38:37.967 --> 38:39.142
I LOVE YOU, DAD.

38:39.839 --> 38:44.974
-[DRAMATIC CHORAL MUSIC]

38:46.585 --> 38:49.892
-[GASPING]

39:11.392 --> 39:16.223
[GASPING AND SHIVERING]

39:26.189 --> 39:31.020
-[AIR HISSING]

39:38.071 --> 39:39.246
-DAD!

39:40.378 --> 39:43.032
-[AIR HISSING]

39:49.822 --> 39:51.258
-DAD!

39:54.217 --> 39:59.048
-[TRIUMPHANT MUSIC]

40:10.190 --> 40:12.801
-[ALL CHEERING]

40:12.932 --> 40:14.499
-DAD, I KNEW YOU'D MAKE IT!

40:14.629 --> 40:16.065
-[ALL CHEERING]

40:16.196 --> 40:17.153
-CAPTAIN THORPE:
COME ON, MITCH, BABY.

40:17.284 --> 40:18.198
-MAN: COME ON, BIG GUY.

40:18.328 --> 40:19.199
WATCH YOUR HEAD.

40:21.767 --> 40:25.553
-[ALL LAUGHING, CHATTERING]

40:26.467 --> 40:27.947
-SHAUNI: WE THOUGHT
WE'D LOST YOU.

40:30.079 --> 40:31.124
-DAD.

40:33.431 --> 40:34.649
I LOVE YOU, DAD.

40:36.825 --> 40:41.613
-[TRIUMPHANT MUSIC]

40:41.743 --> 40:42.962
-LET'S GO HOME, DAD.

40:45.834 --> 40:49.838
-[UPBEAT MUSIC]

40:50.360 --> 40:52.624
-I TOLD CRAIG THAT
THE MONEY THE JOB PAYS

40:52.754 --> 40:55.888
IS NOT NEARLY AS IMPORTANT
AS THE PEOPLE I WORK WITH.

40:56.628 --> 40:58.020
-YEAH.

40:58.543 --> 41:02.024
THAT'S ABOUT WHAT I TOLD MOM,
ABOUT WHO I WANNA LIVE WITH.

41:03.722 --> 41:05.941
-YOU KNOW, SOME REALLY WILD
THINGS WENT THOUGH MY MIND

41:06.072 --> 41:07.334
WHEN I WAS IN THAT CHAMBER.

41:07.856 --> 41:08.683
-LIKE WHAT?

41:10.032 --> 41:11.599
-LIKE BEING OUTSIDE OF MY BODY,

41:11.730 --> 41:13.906
AND LOOKING DOWN ON MYSELF,

41:14.428 --> 41:15.734
AND SEEING EVERYBODY AROUND ME,

41:15.864 --> 41:18.519
BUT NOBODY COULD SEE ME.

41:19.651 --> 41:20.869
-YOU MEAN LIKE A GHOST?

41:21.000 --> 41:21.870
-YEAH.

41:24.220 --> 41:26.005
EXCEPT HE WAS DEAD, I'M NOT.

41:28.268 --> 41:30.096
ARE YOU READY TO BOOGIE?

41:31.097 --> 41:31.967
-YEAH.

41:33.055 --> 41:34.796
BUT DO ME ONE FAVOR, DAD.

41:34.927 --> 41:37.190
DON'T TRY ANY STUNTS THAT
MAKE YOU GO UNDERWATER.

41:38.017 --> 41:38.931
-DON'T WORRY.

41:45.546 --> 41:46.460
I'VE SEEN THE LIGHT.

41:51.291 --> 41:52.553
[LAUGHING]

42:03.390 --> 42:06.262
-[END THEME PLAYING]
